  "question": "Which of the following statement(s) is/are true about benign lesions of the liver?A. Adenomas are true neoplasms with a predisposition for complications and should usually be resected.B. Focal nodular hyperplasia (FNH) is a neoplasm related to birth control pills (BCPs) and usually requires resection.C. Hemangiomas are the most common benign lesions of the liver that come to the surgeon's attention.",
