  "question": "A 45-year-old man with Child-Pugh Class C cirrhosis is found to have a 3 cm mass in the right lobe of the liver. Staging workup confirms the tumor has no vascular invasion or distant metastasis. What is the best treatment option for this patient?",
  "options": {
    "A": "Hepatic resection",
    "B": "| Hepatic Oncology | Hepatocellular Carcinoma \nQuestion 54\nA 45-year-old man with Child-Pugh Class C cirrhosis is found to have a 3 cm mass in the right lobe of the liver. Staging workup confirms the tumor has no vascular invasion or distant metastasis. What is the best treatment option for this patient?",
    "C": "Liver transplantation",
    "D": "Sorafenib therapy",
    "E": "Supportive palliative care"
  },
  "answer": "C) Liver transplantation",
